    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "Imam Muhammad al-Baqir (peace be upon him) presents a comprehensive theological argument that sufficient proof of God's existence is available to people of intellect through eight categories of evidence: divine creation, divine sovereignty, divine majesty, divine light, divine proof, the speech He has given to His servants, the mission of the Prophets, and the revealed scriptures. This hadith is from the first chapter of al-Kafi (Kitab al-'Aql wa'l-Jahl), which establishes rational and theological foundations for knowledge of God. The Imam's teaching here reflects the Shia theological emphasis on the role of 'aql (intellect) as a means for recognizing divine truth.",
        "key_terms": {
          "أُولُو الْأَلْبَابِ": "Those possessing understanding/intellect — a Quranic phrase (e.g., 3:190) denoting those who use their reason",
          "الرَّبِّ الْمُسَخِّرِ": "The Subduing Lord — One who subjugates and controls all of creation",
          "الرَّبِّ الْقَاهِرِ": "The Compelling Lord — al-Qahir is a divine name meaning the All-Subduing, Overwhelming",
          "الرَّبِّ الظَّاهِرِ": "The Manifest Lord — One whose signs are apparent and evident in creation",
          "بُرْهَانِ الرَّبِّ الصَّادِقِ": "The proof of the Truthful Lord — God's proofs are truthful and reliable"
        },
        "seo_question": "What proof does Imam al-Baqir give for the existence of God in al-Kafi?"
      },
      "ur": {
        "summary": "امام محمد باقر علیہ السلام نے آٹھ دلائل بیان کیے جو عقلمندوں کے لیے اللہ کے وجود کی کافی دلیل ہیں: تخلیق، اقتدار، جلال، نور، برہان، بندوں کی گفتگو، رسالت، اور وحی۔ یہ حدیث کتاب الکافی کے پہلے باب سے ہے جو عقل اور جہل کے بارے میں ہے۔",
